4. Empirical Quantile 

quantile(xt,c(.95,.99))
##      95%      99% 
## 2.653783 5.013151
    1. Empirical expected shortfall or CVaR. 1st method
sxt = sort(xt) # Sorting into increasing order
0.95*2515
## [1] 2389.25
(es=sum(sxt[2390:2515])/(2515-2389))# ES 0.95
## [1] 3.994857
0.99*2515
## [1] 2489.85
(es=sum(sxt[2490:2515])/(2515-2489))# ES 0.99
## [1] 6.074108
    1. Empirical expected shortfall or CVaR. 2nd method
idx=c(1:2515)[xt >= 2.653783]
mean(xt[idx])
## [1] 3.994857
idx1=c(1:2515)[xt >= 5.013151]
mean(xt[idx1])
## [1] 6.074108
  • Empirical median shortfall
median(xt[idx])
## [1] 3.527853
median(xt[idx1])
## [1] 5.781306
